			<h2>This is a Safe Space for You</h2>
		</header>
		<p class="jerk_p">Some people are jerks.  But the word ‘jerk’ doesn’t even begin to describe someone who sexually assaults you. This is not a place for them.</p>
		<p>This site is a place for you*, the survivor of that horrible sexual assault, to come together with another survivor. Talk, bond, draw together...with our site, you’ll share a unique and anonymous conversation with another survivor over a 1:1 audio chat while painting on a shared online canvas. It’s fun...but don’t take our word for it; take it out for a spin yourself. Or check out some of the <a href="#gallery">past creations</a>.</p>
		<p class="postscript_p">*And yes, this means that if you’re not a survivor of sexual assault, this is not the place for you. We’re sorry, but we need to respect the privacy of survivors. If you want to talk, call the <a href="http://www.ywca.org/site/c.cuIRJ7NTKrLaG/b.8778673/k.2A72/Domestic_Violence_and_Violence_Against_Women.html">YWCA</a> at (800) 572-2782.</p>

